race.comment: EMPIRE GRACE (4) had their measure last start when returning to winning form in fine style over this track and trip. Peaking now and well placed to go on with the job. LUCKY FORTUNA (6) went forward and proved too strong last time at Murray Bridge. Faces a tricky draw but has found form and is well positioned to continue progressing. EXPLICABLE (2) wound up strongly to finish third over this track and trip last start. Kept fresh with 38 days between runs and gets in well with the claim. Capable of going a couple better. TYUSIX (10) resumes and has jumped out well in readiness. In nicely at the weights with the claimer aboard and should make her presence felt. GRINZINGER ACE (5) chased in vain behind EMPIRE GRACE here two weeks ago when well supported. Rises in weight without the claim, making it harder to turn the tables, but draws well and deserves respect.
